<br>
A loud crash and the sudden feeling of cool liquid splattering over her sent her jumping as the waitress tripped and spilled the drinks Radgen had ordered for them all over her.  Gasping in surprise the sudden accident breaks her current chain of thought and she looks up and tries to calm the flustered waitress.<br>
<br>
"I am so sorry, Ma'am, let me get you a towel and the drinks are on the house." the young girl stammered.<br>
<br>
"Hush it is nothing my clothing needed washing anyways so don't you worry, however if you could arrange with the inn keeper a room for me tonight that would be appreciated.  I have the platinum and if a bath could be prepared in the room for me also in about an hour.  I would be indebted to you,"  Lodach spoke calmly and the girl relaxed.<br>
<br>
"Thank you ma'am, I will bring fresh drinks."<br>
<br>
Lodach turned and looked at Radgen, sighing in resignation at the gleam of humor in his eyes.<br>
<br>
"Well I am glad you find a wine stain on my cloak so amusing, you could have at least of offered help."<br>
<br>
Radgen quietly speaks while a small smirk forms on his lips, "Normally you know me to be more attentive, but you seem to be handling the situation well enough with out me, and anyways I warned you I wasn't good company tonight."<br>
<br>
Lodach sits down with a exhasberated sigh and watches accross the room the young girl prepare her drink and wonders why she looks so familiar to her. <p>Lodach Trueheart, High Priestess Of Rodcet Nife<BR>
